Comment.Text: An FFT is applied on each window thanks to the Spectral Analysis box.
The Signal Display box is just present to monitor the input of the spectrum computation pipeline. The Window Manager is used to organize the two windows correctly !
Then the Temporal Filter box filters the signal in the [1 40] Hz range.
The CSV File Reader box reads CSV file containing signals.
The Acquisition client box reads CSV file containing signals.
Each channel is referenced against channel Nz (which was recorded on the nose in the demonstrated file) thanks to the Reference Channel box.
Finally, the Power Spectrum Display displays the resulting spectrum.
You can browse each box' documentation by selecting the box and pressing F1
The Time Based Epoching box splits the signals in blocks of 1 seconds every 16th of second. This is a moving window.
